President Cyril Ramaphosa delivers his 2023 State of the Nation Address at the Cape Town City Hall. AFP/Esa Alexander JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has dismissed the criticism of the position of Minister of Electricity, saying it is misguided. Ramaphosa will appoint the minister to be based in the Presidency. This is government's latest attempt to deal with the country's worsening electricity crisis. READ: President to appoint electricity minister On Thursday, the president declared a national state of disaster over the electricity crisis with immediate effect. He said the state of disaster will exempt critical infrastructure including hospitals and water treatment plants from rolling blackouts. President Cyril Ramaphosa will appoint a new Minister of Electricity to be based in the presidency. This is government's latest attempt to deal with the country's worsening electricity crisis. The president has dismissed the criticism on this new position, saying it's misguided. pic.twitter.com/9KrHDI9yw8